frameDefinitions: This frame characterizes the likelihood that a Hypothetical_event will happen as a position on a scale of impossible to inevitable.
A State_of_affairs has held and continues to hold up to the Reference_occasion.
Due to internal forces/properties, an Entity is inclined towards a particular Behavior, which may be to perform an action or to maintain a state.
An Item is located on a Scale relative to a critical value which is determined by some Enabled_situation.
An Agent uses a Resource which is consumed and unavailable for future use.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
frameExamples: <t>To date</t>, the Department already has numerous requests for new systems to be developed.
We <t>exhausted</t> our supply of oil long ago.
It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
listRoleDefinitions: A numerical representation of the probability that a Hypothetical_event will occur.
A metaphorical representation of the position on the scale of likelihood that the Hypothetical_event will occur.
The event that is expected to happen with a certain likelihood.
A state which holds prior to and up through the <fen>Reference_occasion</fen>.
The time or event (normally speech time) with respect to which the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is located.
TheFrame Element <fen>Entity</fen> identifies the person or thing that has a tendency towards some Behaviour.
The role <fen>Behavior</fen> marks expressions that indicate which state or action the <fen>Entity</fen> tends towards.
The entity whose scalar property is specified.
The <fen>Scale</fen> is the attribute of the <fen>Item</fen> that is being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Enabled_situation</fen> by which the critical value is judged.
The <fen>Resource</fen> is exhausted over time by being used.
The degree to which the Resource is depleted by the Agent.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> exhausts the <fen>Resource</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> exhausts the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
listRoleExamples: There's a <fex>95 %</fex> chance of rain today.
Chances are <fex>slim</fex> that he'll pull through.
He's got a small chance <fex>of making it out alive</fex>.
<fex>How is your course going</fex> so far?
She was loving and concerned about others up to <fex>her dying breath</fex>.
<fex>Lubomir</fex> was not inclined to believe me
Martha has a tendency <fex>to overdo the housekeeping</fex>.
It was <fex>hot</fex> enough to ignite the iron.
Can He make a rock too heavy <fex>for Him to lift</fex>?
Their program used up <fex>very little</fex> processing power.
<fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: the early part of the century
